  "title": "Electrical Engineer (West) - Up to $4200",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>· Design control systems.</p><p>· Preparation of drawings for customer approval.</p><p>· Preparation of drawings/BCM for shop floor production.</p><p>· Co-ordinating with clients, consultants and internal department.</p><p>· Drafting work with use of CAD system (AUTOCAD/SOLIDWORKS).</p><p>· Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned.<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Diploma or Bachelor’s Degree in Electrical Engineering.</p><p>· Hands on experience with vessel mechanical and engine systems.</p><p>· Experience with engineering design software.</p><p>· Familiarity with maritime HM&E systems and naval construction processes.</p><p>· Excellent analytical thinking and problem-solving abilities.</p><p>· Team player and good communication skills.</p><p>· Physically fit and able to work in strenuous circumstances.<br /><br /><strong>Interested and suitable candidate kindly click quick apply. Resume will be forwarded to Stepfan Soon Yit</strong></p><p><strong>We regret that only suitable candidate will be notified.</strong></p><p><strong>GEMS Recruit/EA License : 23C1459</strong></p><p><strong>EA Personnel No : R24120893 (Stepfan Soon Yit)</strong></p>",
